sub_title: Partner at THNK | Board Member | Executive Coach | Leadership Development Expert | Speaker
summary:
Natasha’s passion is around the development of individuals, teams, and organizations, while working at the interface of business strategy and personal leadership. She specializes in supporting leaders during times of challenge and change - working with leaders on an individual basis, in team settings and in dedicated leadership development initiatives.

Natasha is Partner at THNK School of Creative Leadership. Her recent work experience includes being Head of Organization Development at Jones Lang LaSalle in Asia-Pacific, Organization Leadership Consultant at IBM in Asia-Pacific and Strategy Consultant at McKinsey. She has lived and worked in the Netherlands, France, Japan, Singapore, and Turkey.   
Natasha holds an MSc in Molecular Biology and an MBA from INSEAD. She is also a certified Integral Coach, Enneagram and Systemic Practitioner.
